00:06:11.560 --> 00:06:15.510
other books on Madison, but
also presidential issues.

00:06:15.510 --> 00:06:20.630
I think there's a book on
the Lincoln presidency.

00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:29.080
And then, to my closer left is Mary
Sarah Bilder, a professor of law

00:06:29.080 --> 00:06:35.510
and distinguished scholar at Boston
College in Boston, Massachusetts.

00:06:35.510 --> 00:06:42.340
And Mary is particularly a poster
child for the Library of Congress

00:06:42.340 --> 00:06:46.880
because not only has she done
work on a research on Madison here

00:06:46.880 --> 00:06:50.190
within our extraordinary
collections which Jim Hutson,

00:06:50.190 --> 00:06:53.030
the chief of the Manuscript
Division will talk to you

00:06:53.030 --> 00:06:54.770
