01:16:02.250 --> 01:16:04.790
Shaffer: Well, this has been an
extraordinary morning for me.

01:16:04.790 --> 01:16:11.300 position:56%
I have learned so much about Madison
beyond what I knew as a young child

01:16:11.300 --> 01:16:15.470
that he was the first one to
think about creating a library

01:16:15.470 --> 01:16:21.520
for Congress at the
Continental Congress in 1783.

01:16:21.520 --> 01:16:24.330
And then also that of course,
he was the sitting president

01:16:24.330 --> 01:16:28.460
when we purchased Jefferson's
books and I always believed--

01:16:28.460 --> 01:16:33.150
and John Cole, the library's
phenomenal historian can correct me

01:16:33.150 --> 01:16:36.500
for posterity, but I think the
must have had a role in that.

01:16:36.500 --> 01:16:41.070
But I've learned so much including
David when the origination

01:16:41.070 --> 01:16:44.990
of power couple came
into being in Washington.

01:16:44.990 --> 01:16:49.740 position:56%
So, that was just a fabulous morning
to learn more about Jefferson--

